1
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:40,155 --> 00:01:42,340
(Shanghao House's Veteran Soldier)
Liangyuan.

3
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:44,590
When I was ten years younger...

4
00:01:44,590 --> 00:01:46,070
(February, Ba Bridge, Chang'an)

5
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:48,710
I wanted to make a name for myself
in Chang'an

6
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:50,000
and serve the imperial court.

7
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,430
Unfortunately, I was unlucky.

8
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,755
Whether submitting my writings
or taking the imperial exams,

9
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,920
nothing worked.

10
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,120
By the 10th year of Tianbao,

11
00:01:59,310 --> 00:02:00,760
I still achieved nothing.

12
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:04,000
On my 40th birthday,

13
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:08,430
my friend invited me

14
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:10,088
to sail at Qujiang River to celebrate.

15
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,030
The boat was halfway through

16
00:02:12,430 --> 00:02:14,430
when a thick fog
suddenly rose from the shore.

17
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:16,870
This scene

18
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,190
instantly threw me into despair.

19
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:23,910
Isn't this my life?

20
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:26,840
It's halfway through,

21
00:02:27,910 --> 00:02:31,120
but my future is still uncertain.

22
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:33,910
I got off the boat,

23
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:37,190
feeling utterly lost.

24
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,750
Before I knew it,

25
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:42,470
I walked to Shanghao House,

26
00:02:42,710 --> 00:02:44,680
500 meters outside Chunming Gate

27
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:46,430
in the east of the city.

28
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:49,190
The name

29
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,590
doesn't sound good

30
00:02:53,430 --> 00:02:55,240
and can't even be called a house.

31
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,120
It's just a mass grave.

32
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:00,800
I

33
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,400
picked a grave

34
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,630
and lay in it.

35
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:09,311
I don't know how long I lay there.

36
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,030
A veteran soldier

37
00:03:12,030 --> 00:03:13,750
guarding the grave came.

38
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,520
That guy

39
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:19,680
seemed battered by life,

40
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,470
and one of his eyes was blind.

41
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,560
He lived in seclusion in Shanghao House.

42
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,150
He said

43
00:03:27,888 --> 00:03:29,533
he was guarding the grave

44
00:03:29,555 --> 00:03:31,680
of his brother
who was forced to be killed.

45
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:35,800
He told me

46
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:38,240
he was forced to join the army

47
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:41,222
to guard the borders of Western Regions

48
00:03:41,710 --> 00:03:43,190
when he was just as tall as a horse.

49
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,800
It was his first time

50
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,960
leaving his family
and going to the battlefield.

51
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:53,680
He didn't know when he would die.

52
00:03:55,630 --> 00:03:56,630
One day

53
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:58,800
on the battlefield,

54
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,840
a brutal enemy

55
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,840
had him pinned down.

56
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,444
Since he was about to be killed,

57
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,280
he went feral

58
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,590
and ripped off

59
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,910
the enemy's cheek with his teeth.

60
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,622
He managed to strike back
with that move.

61
00:04:16,630 --> 00:04:17,600
Since that battle,

62
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,800
the veteran figured it out.

63
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,480
Since he was in a desperate situation

64
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,711
with no way to retreat,

65
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,750
why not take a step forward

66
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:27,688
and fight to the death?

67
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:28,920
Maybe

68
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,000
he could find

69
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,310
a glimmer of hope.

70
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,480
From that day on,

71
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:37,160
he practiced swordsmanship and riding.

72
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,240
Whenever the horn rang,

73
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,830
he would rush down from a high place,

74
00:04:41,830 --> 00:04:43,270
bend down and grab the army flag.

75
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:47,870
With this unyielding spirit,

76
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,680
he survived hundreds of battles,

77
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,950
returned to Chang'an

78
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,190
from Western Regions,

79
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,430
and became Shadow Chief
of Wannian County.

80
00:04:58,430 --> 00:04:59,510
I was greatly shocked

81
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,270
to hear this.

82
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:03,950
I wonder

83
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,310
how my situation

84
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,160
compares to that of the veteran...

85
00:05:10,630 --> 00:05:12,720
He could strike one blow on fate,

86
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,270
why can't I?

87
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,560
Please.

