118
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,822
The horses can't run anymore.

119
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:17,844
We humans can still run.

120
00:07:17,844 --> 00:07:18,720
- Yes.
- Yes.

121
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,830
- I can run too.
- I can run too.

122
00:07:21,430 --> 00:07:22,120
I can run too.

123
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,630
We haven't rested for five days.

124
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:27,510
Our bodies can't handle

125
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,510
this heavy burden.

126
00:07:30,430 --> 00:07:31,070
Mr. Li.

127
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,070
I usually

128
00:07:32,111 --> 00:07:33,488
transport goods in the mountains.

129
00:07:33,511 --> 00:07:34,155
I can run!

130
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:35,560
I can run too!

131
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:38,120
I've never met

132
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,630
a serious official like you.

133
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:40,600
These days

134
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,120
have been hard for you.

135
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,160
How about this? I volunteer to help,

136
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,240
but I can't finish the whole journey.

137
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:53,830
What are you doing?

138
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:55,920
What are you doing?

139
00:07:56,178 --> 00:07:57,600
What does this have to do with you?

140
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,120
Shut up!

141
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,311
We're doing an experiment!

142
00:07:59,377 --> 00:08:01,510
If you break Mr. Li's jars,

143
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,822
and affect the results
of the experiment,

144
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:06,000
you'll affect His Majesty's
litchi consumption!

145
00:08:07,190 --> 00:08:09,360
How many heads do you have to lose?

146
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:09,800
No.

147
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,920
You're wrong.

148
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:12,560
The people helped

149
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,890
to relieve His Majesty's burdens.

150
00:08:14,444 --> 00:08:15,933
If you won't let them do the relay,

151
00:08:15,955 --> 00:08:17,066
can you give me a horse?

152
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:17,730
Yes.

153
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:19,133
- That's right.
- Can you give it?

154
00:08:19,155 --> 00:08:21,120
Mr. Li, our horses

155
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,560
are all registered army horses,

156
00:08:22,622 --> 00:08:24,090
responsible for patrolling the border.

157
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:25,466
How can I lend it out so easily?

158
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,644
You won't allow me to use the people
or lend horses to me.

159
00:08:27,688 --> 00:08:28,600
How should I experiment?

160
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,140
- Yes.
- Yes.

161
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,310
You can't ask me about this.

162
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,950
I'm only responsible for serving you

163
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,320
and ensuring safety.

164
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,240
I should ask you.

165
00:08:35,444 --> 00:08:37,177
Are you going to continue
this experiment?

166
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,080
If not,

167
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:39,870
I'll lift the ban on Small East Gate

168
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:41,240
and report back.

169
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,820
Aren't you
making things difficult for me?

170
00:08:42,822 --> 00:08:43,320
Get lost!

171
